  "origin": {
    "question": "Problem 8.3. In 3-dimensional Euclidean space, what is a necessary and sufficient condition on a field of one-forms $\\tilde{\\sigma}$ for there to exist a function $f$ such that $\\tilde{\\sigma} = \\widetilde{\\mathrm{df}}$ ?",
    "answer": "$\\\\sigma_{i,j} = \\\\sigma_{j,i}$ (或等价表述为向量场 $\\\\pmb{\\\\sigma}$ 的旋量为零)",
    "solution": "In a cartesian coordinate basis the condition is that $\\sigma_{i,j} = \\sigma_{j,i}$ . This is equivalent to the basis-free requirement that the curl of $\\pmb{\\sigma}$ (the vector equivalent of $\\tilde{\\pmb{\\sigma}}$ ) vanish."
  },
